sect1.para:
Talcott Parsons, a sociologist practicing within the United States, developed the theory of social systems. The social systems theory (Parsons, 
               1951
            ) explores the various roles held in society and the expectations placed on these roles and the persons who assume them in varied situations. The sick role, one of the roles identified by Parsons (Parsons, 
               1975
            ), is assumed by persons once labeled with an illness or diagnosis.
